$ VBScript: writing colored output to the console

This is an attempt to create a → development/languages/VBScript[VB Script] that creates colored output on the console when run with → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cscript_exe[`cscript.exe`].

gh|about-VBScript|/examples/colored-output.vbs||

sa:
 → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/subsystem/console#win-virtual-terminal-sequences[Virtual Terminal Sequences on Windows]

  The value of → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/console#reg-console-VirtualTerminalLevel[`VirtualTerminalLevel`] under the registry key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/console[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Console`].

links:
    → https://stackoverflow.com/a/38815213/180275[This stackoverflow answer] was very useful.
